  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reviving the transport and maize marketing business in Chingola District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Establish a clear long-term strategy and vision that helps CDCU focus on making its transport and marketing business profitable.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Planned activities:
Strategic Planning: assist CDCU in developing a SMART strategic plan guiding CDCU in its transport and marketing business through clear strategic objectives and targets and supported by a budget and cash flow projection.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The assessment team concluded on a brief cooperation with CDCU in 2018  following an assessment of the Union in October  2018. The collaboration is conditional on CDCU submitting an action plan by mid-October that outlines how CDCU will revive its transport business so that it will be profitable again within the next 3 months.
CDCU has 43 paid-up Primary Cooperative members  representing around 2 000 farmers in the district. CDCU runs a transport business focused on input distribution to members and crop marketing of members&apos; produce  particularly maize. Thanks to government contracts  CDCU was running profitably up to 2017. But due to government policy changes and truck failures  the business went down and now needs to be revived.
BHAG 2018: A profitable transport business based on a SMART strategic business plan  serving at least 20% of members through direct marketing and 80% of members through market linkage facilitation.
The project will focus on Strategic Planning to guide CDCU in its transport and marketing business through clear strategic objectives and targets and supported by a budget and cash flow projection.</narrative>
  </description>
